HEADWORD: catechol
<hw>cat"e*chol</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧t"⟦ecr⟧*k⟦add⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[.]</ety> <def>any of a group of chemicals having a benzene ring
substituted with two hydroxyl groups in ortho position, especially
ortho-dihydroxybenzene itself (<chform>C6H6O2</chform>), also called
<altname>pyrocatechol</altname>, used in photography and as a
reagent.</def>⟦br⟧
